Gunmen have reportedly killed five persons and injured three others in some communities of Irigwe chiefdom of Bassa Local Government Area of Plateau State. Mr Davidson Malison, National Publicity Secretary, Iregwe Development Association, said yesterday in Jos that the attack took place on Monday.   Police probe murder of teenage girl in Ebonyi     Terrorists set octogenarian ablaze in Niger     Police foil hoodlums’ attack on Dangote refinery   Malison said the assailants, who struck in the night, destroyed a vehicle and took away some motorcycles. Police spokesman Ubah Ogaba confirmed the incident, adding that a statement would be issued soon on the incident. Maj. Ishaku Takwa, Media Officer of Operation Safe Haven, said, “I don’t have the details.”